<div class="welcome-header">
  <h1>Welcome to StreamFinder</h1>
</div>

<div class="welcome-container">
  <div class="p2 bg-white rounded my2 mx-auto welcome-text">
    <h3>An application geared towards environmental consultants and scientists looking to:</h3>
      <li>Find reference reaches for environmental restoration projects</li><br>
      <li>Find stream, wetland, and subsurface monitoring stations throughout Colorado</li><br>
      <li>Search for stations by watershed (HUC 8)</li><br>
      <li>Search for stream stations by drainage area</li><br>
      <li>Obtain historic streamflow data</li>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="p2 bg-white rounded my2 mx-auto welcome-text">
  <p>The station data is retrieved from the <a href="https://www.waterqualitydata.us/webservices_documentation/" target="_blank">Water Quality Portal Web Service</a> and made available in an easy to navigate map interface.</p>
  <p>By adding monitoring stations to a particular project, users can:</p>
     <li>View recent (24-hr) streamflow</li><br>
     <li>Perform a query for historical streamflow</li><br>
     <li>Have streamflow data emailed for further analysis</li><br>
  <p>Historical data is provided by way of the <a href="https://waterservices.usgs.gov/rest/IV-Service.html" target="_blank">USGS Water Data Web Service.</a></p>
</div>

