<div class="historical-section">
  <div class="p2 rounded my2 mx-auto historical-summary">
    <p>The map to the right shows the major western water districts identified by John Wesley Powell in 1890.</p><br>
    <p>Powell was a civil war veteran and early American explorer of the western territories (led the first documented passage through the Grand Canyon).  Powell argued to congress in 1877 that future western states should be divided by these districts, stating: "Gentlemen, you are piling up a heritage of conflict and litigation over water rights, for there is not sufficient water to supply the land."</p><br>
    <p>This impressive foresight provides an interesting thought experiment about well planned environmental regulation and what it means to be a citizen of a state.</p>
  </div>

